The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Jan. 25: Nokia has bagged an order to manage Hutchison Essar?s mobile network in nine circles for five years, for which it would take on board 600 employees from its client. The circles include Gujarat, Karnataka, Andhra Pradesh, Chennai, Uttar Pradesh, Rajasthan, Haryana and Bengal.

 Mumbai, Jan. 25: Torrent Pharmaceuticals Ltd will split its shares with a face value of Rs 10 each in a ratio of 1:2. After the stock split, the company will issue one bonus share for each one held, Torrent Pharma has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 New Delhi, Jan. 25: The Central Electricity Regulatory Commission (CERC) will fix a margin of 4 paise per unit for electricity traders, a decision which will hit the revenues PTC India, Tata Power Trading and Adani Exports.

 New Delhi, Jan. 25: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh today invited businessmen from Saudi Arabia to invest in India?s infrastructure sector, including airports and railways.

 New Delhi, Jan. 25: The customs, excise and service tax appellate tribunal has ruled that Toyota Kirloskar Motors will not be liable to pay customs duty on the royalty it pays to its Japanese parent for technical expertise and imported spare parts.




